  "notes": "Northwestern Catalan (Lleidatà/Pallarès). Western block, spoken in Lleida and Pyrenean valleys. No schwa reduction: 7-vowel system fully maintained in unstressed positions (unlike Eastern Catalan). Open-e /ɛ/ and open-o /ɔ/ preserved as distinct phonemes. Palatal lateral /ʎ/ preserved without yeísmo. Rhotic /ɾ/ may be trilled [r] in some contexts (word-initial, post-nasal). Closest to Valencian in vowel system.",
